28/04/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The education ministry on Tuesday (27 April) presented the national programme for the development of education from the preschool to the university level.
It envisions introduction of state exams for all students and creation of an institute for headmasters.
The final version of the strategy will be drafted by June 2005 and then approved by the government and parliament.
(Dnevnik - 28/04/04;
A1 TV - 27/04/04)
